<p><b>Frederick James "Freddie" Perren</b> (May 15, 1943 – December 16, 2004) was an American <a href="Songwriter" title="Songwriter">songwriter</a>, <a href="Record_producer" title="Record producer">record producer</a>, <a href="Arranger" title="Arranger" class="mw-redirect">arranger</a>, and <a href="Orchestra_conductor" title="Orchestra conductor" class="mw-redirect">orchestra conductor</a> best known as co-songwriter and co-producer of such mega-hits as "<a href="Boogie_Fever" title="Boogie Fever">Boogie Fever</a>" by <a href="The_Sylvers" title="The Sylvers">the Sylvers</a>, "<a href="I_Will_Survive" title="I Will Survive">I Will Survive</a>" by <a href="Gloria_Gaynor" title="Gloria Gaynor">Gloria Gaynor</a>, and "<a href="Shake_Your_Groove_Thing" title="Shake Your Groove Thing">Shake Your Groove Thing</a>" by <a href="Peaches_&_Herb" title="Peaches &amp; Herb">Peaches &amp; Herb</a>.</p>
